A courier company responsible for dumping COVID-19 test kits in the Eastern Cape, has been fired. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Funeral parlours have had to change the way they operate during the time of COVID-19. Identifying and certifying corpses have become a challenge with no clear regulations on how this should be done while staying safe. READ: SA lockdown: Cogta announces changes to funeral regulations One of the ways in which a body is identified is by taking fingerprints, but this has become a headache for funeral parlours as there are no clear regulations on how to do this safely. Another nightmare is the sheer number of corpses coming to the Eastern Cape from the Western Cape, currently the epicentre of the COVID-19 outbreak in South Africa. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.